700 m from the Alexandre Dumas metro station (L2), this superb space dedicated to the promotion of contemporary sculpture is to be discovered: a free place and open to all. Until 15.12.2024, the exhibition "Imaginary worlds" is being held there (strange animals, forest, palm beach, etc. await you). An incredible and astonishing visit guaranteed!

Second time going there, and still just as interesting. The works on display are truly out of another world. The places are perfectly arranged. The free nature of this foundation is pleasant. Please note there is no elevator but a small staircase with a ramp that is still accessible

This exhibition space is just great. It's free. The staff are lovely. There is even a quiz available for younger children. The quality of the exhibition during our visit was impeccable, it was very interesting.

A very nice place where you will spend some time. The staff is welcoming and attentive, the current exhibition is enriching and the place is very cozy!! You can leave your belongings at the entrance in lockers secured by a code and all you have to do is enjoy the works of art.
